relation: Adds an element to another element's subtree.
Adds an event handler for a named event on the HTML Document Object Model (DOM).
Removes an event handler from a named event on the HTML Document Object Model (DOM).
Tests if the supplied object is equal to the current element. (Overrides Object.Equals(Object).)
Puts user input focus on the current element.

textBeforeTable: Methods Top Gets the name of the HTML tag. TagName Gets or sets the location of this element in the tab order. TabIndex Gets or sets a semicolon-delimited list of styles for the current element. Style Gets or sets the distance between the edge of the element and the top edge of its content. ScrollTop Gets the dimensions of an element's scrollable region. ScrollRectangle Gets or sets the distance between the edge of the element and the left edge of its content. ScrollLeft Gets the current element's parent element. Parent Gets or sets the current element's text. OuterText Gets or sets the current element's HTML code.
textAfterTable: Top Events   Name Description Click Occurs when the user clicks on the element with the left mouse button. DoubleClick Occurs when the user clicks the left mouse button over an element twice, in rapid succession. Drag Occurs when the user drags text to various locations. DragEnd Occurs when a user finishes a drag operation. DragLeave Occurs when the user is no longer dragging an item over this element. DragOver Occurs when the user drags text over the element. Focusing Occurs when the element first receives user input focus. GotFocus Occurs when the element has received user input
